text: For the ECS data to be processable, it has to be assigned to a Reprocessing Group and be in status New . The Reprocessing Group is then selected in the ECS collection agent of the reprocessing workflow. For ECS data to be processed, it must be assigned to a Reprocessing Group and have a status of New. The Reprocessing Group is then selected within the ECS collection agent as part of the reprocessing workflow. This section has the following subsections: ECS - Creating a Reprocessing Group ECS - Searching for a Reprocessing Group ECS - Deleting a Reprocessing Group
title: Managing ECS Reprocessing Groups - MediationZone Documentation 9.4 - InfoZone
